<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-11T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-11T06:00:00-05:00" n="953" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d953">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.7211</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-11T12:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1916, noon</hi></date>. <lb/>
                                    [<hi rend="italic">Received 12.43 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1590. Serbian Minister at Paris desires me to ascertain whether the
                            nomination of Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ML1">Lioubomir
                                Michaїlovitch</persName> as Envoy Extraordinary and Minister
                            Plenipotentiary of Serbia to the United States will be agreeable to our
                                Government.<note n="1" xml:id="d953fn1">Serbia had no diplomatic
                                representative in the United States.</note> He was formerly Serbian
                            Minister to Montenegro.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>